@Jayofthezero: I have a more advanced idea. Basically in steps:
1. A user create a site, then he is the owner (as the actual model);
2. The owner opens the site as democratic;
3. From "owner" role, its changed to "only delegate" role
4. A user submits a pull request (or "update") to the site;
5. The only delegate approves the pull request;
6. The author of the approve pull request turns itself into a delegate of the site, then he have voting rights. Then the site have 2 delegates. And the number can grow.

This is my idea from my Gitcratic project.

